# Intra-Package Import Discipline

## Rule

Within the same package, every import must point to the **real source file**, never to a barrel `index.ts` in the same package.

Barrel `index.ts` files are the **public API surface for external consumers** (other packages). They must not be used as import targets inside the package that owns them.

## Why

- Importing through a barrel inside the same package creates circular dependency risks.
- It makes the dependency graph opaque: readers cannot tell which symbol comes from which module.
- It increases the chance of accidental re-export conflicts when barrels are updated.

## Good

```ts
// src/domains/group/events/GroupCreatedEvent.ts
import { IdentityAccessDomainEventSchema } from '../../types/IdentityAccessDomainEventSchema';

// src/domains/role/events/RoleCreatedEvent.ts
import { DescriptionSchema, NameSchema } from '../../types/base-schema';

// src/user/UserEntity.ts — importing a peer aggregate directly
import { UserRepositoryPort } from './ports/UserRepositoryPort';
import { buildUserCreatedEvent } from './events/buildUserCreatedEvent';
import { UserCreateCommand } from './commands/UserCreateCommand';
```

## Bad

```ts
// ❌ Never import through a barrel inside the same package

// src/domains/group/events/GroupCreatedEvent.ts
import { IdentityAccessDomainEventSchema } from '../../types'; // ← barrel of sibling folder

// src/user/UserEntity.ts
import { buildUserCreatedEvent } from './events'; // ← barrel of sibling subfolder
import { UserCreateCommand } from './commands';    // ← barrel of sibling subfolder
import { UserRepositoryPort } from './ports';      // ← barrel of sibling subfolder
```

## Scope

This rule applies **only within a package**. When importing from another package (e.g. `@aor/common`, `@aor/domain`), always import from the package root or its published entry-point — i.e., the barrel is the correct target for cross-package imports.

```ts
// ✅ Cross-package: import from the package entry-point (barrel is correct here)
import { AccessTokenType } from '@aor/common';
import { ICommandUseCase } from '@aor/domain';

// ✅ Intra-package: import from the real source file
import { buildUserCreatedEvent } from './events/buildUserCreatedEvent';
```

## Summary Table

| Context | Target |
|---|---|
| Same package, same folder | `./RealFile` |
| Same package, sibling subfolder | `./subfolder/RealFile` |
| Same package, parent folder | `../RealFile` |
| Different package | Package entry-point (barrel) |
